  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-decision-001",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-lab-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU1 (CPB hemolysis worst-case identification, Class II, MRL 2) is accepted based on the following structured evidence: (1) All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels — discretization error and use error both exceed requirements, providing additional confidence margin. (2) The two scoped-out factors (test samples, equivalency of input parameters) are appropriately excluded per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 for MRL 2 with documented justification and supporting sensitivity analyses. (3) Three independent validation results (hemolysis index, pressure-flow curve, shear stress distribution) all demonstrate agreement within pre-specified acceptance thresholds, with complete uncertainty quantification and provenance chains. (4) The primary regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate device) is met at all 5 operating points with mean NIH prediction error of 8.3%, well within the 15% threshold. (5) Model form uncertainty was bounded through turbulence model sensitivity analysis; the selected k-ω SST model is appropriate for the flow regime. (6) Software quality assurance, code verification, and iterative convergence documentation collectively ensure computational reliability. The totality of evidence supports submission-level confidence that the CFD model correctly identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for this Class II CPB device under the defined COU.",
